## FULL FEATURE LIST (from Lab 2 Requirements Analysis)

### Group 1 — Account Management
- UC-1.1 Register Account (includes email verification trigger)
- UC-1.2 Verify Email
- UC-1.3 Request New Verification Link (rate-limited)
- UC-1.4 Log In (audit log, lock after 5 failures)
- UC-1.5 Reset Password (1hr token expiry, unlocks account)
- UC-1.6 Resend Verification Link

### Group 2 — Dashboard & Settings
- UC-2.1 View Dashboard (role-aware tabs: Home, My Learning, My Tutoring, Notifications)
- UC-2.2 Manage Privacy Settings (name display, planning area visibility, notification prefs)
- UC-2.3 Receive Notifications (mandatory alerts always delivered; optional can be opted out)

### Group 3 — Tutoring Request Flow (Tutee)
- UC-3.1 Submit Tutoring Request → triggers UC-3.2 + UC-3.3
- UC-3.2 Specify Learning Needs (level, subjects, topics, areas, time slots, duration, urgency)
- UC-3.3 View Recommended Tutors (matching algorithm, ranked 0–100)
- UC-3.4 Select Tutor and Send Request → creates messaging channel
- UC-3.5 Reject Recommended Tutors
- UC-3.6 Broaden Search Criteria → re-run matching
- UC-3.7 Cancel Tutoring Request

### Group 4 — Tutor Management
- UC-4.1 Configure Tutor Profile
- UC-4.2 Set/Update Availability (weekly grid, 1-hour slots)
- UC-4.3 Activate/Deactivate Tutor Mode
- UC-4.4 View Incoming Tutoring Requests
- UC-4.5 Accept Tutoring Request → triggers UC-4.7
- UC-4.6 Decline Tutoring Request
- UC-4.7 Propose Time Slot(s) → triggers UC-5.2

### Group 5 — Session Coordination
- UC-5.1 Coordinate Session via Messaging (block contact info; read-only after completion)
- UC-5.2 Confirm Proposed Time Slot → triggers UC-5.3
- UC-5.3 Select/Confirm Venue (system recommendation or manual)
- UC-5.4 Specify Manual Venue (public location only)
- UC-5.5 Specify Manual Time Slot (via messaging, then update preferred slots)

### Group 6 — Payment & Session Completion
- UC-6.1 Initiate Payment → triggers UC-6.2
- UC-6.2 Display Computed Session Fee (deterministic, server-side)
- UC-6.3 Mark Session Outcome — Tutee (Attended or No-Show: Tutor)
- UC-6.4 Mark Session Outcome — Tutor (Attended or No-Show: Tutee)
- UC-6.5 Submit Session Rating and Review (1–5 stars, standout traits, max 500 chars)
- UC-6.6 Dispute No-Show Status

### Group 7 — Complaints & Appeals
- UC-7.1 Submit Complaint (category + description max 500 chars)
- UC-7.2 Submit Penalty Appeal (within configurable appeal window)
- UC-7.3 Admin: Review Complaints; Record Actions
- UC-7.4 Admin: Review Penalty Appeals; Decide Outcome

### Group 8 — Admin Analytics
- UC-8.1 View Admin Overview Dashboard (KPIs, alerts, session trend chart, top subjects)
- UC-8.2 View Demand Analytics (requests by subject, trending topics, by planning area)
- UC-8.3 View Supply Analytics (tutor counts, workload bands, tutors-by-subject table)
- UC-8.4 View Supply-Demand Gap Analysis (shortage %, recommendations)
- UC-8.5 Export Analytics Data (CSV or Excel, respects active filters)

---

## HOW TO WRITE PLAN.md

When generating PLAN.md, structure it exactly like this:

```
# PeerLearn — PLAN.md

## Status Legend
- [ ] Not started
- [~] In progress
- [x] Done
- [P] Partial — frontend UI exists, needs backend wiring

## Phase 0 — Scaffolding & Infrastructure
### Backend
- [ ] Task
### Frontend
- [ ] Task
### Database
- [ ] Task

## Phase 1 — Account Management
...

## Phase N — ...

## API Route Index
(full list of all REST routes with HTTP method, path, auth requirement)

## State Machine Reference
(session states as a quick-reference block)

## Coding Rules
(the 10 hard rules from above, condensed)
```

Each task must be:
- **Atomic**: one PR, one responsibility
- **Traceable**: reference the UC number (e.g., `UC-3.3`)
- **Specific**: say exactly what endpoint, component, or function to build
- For partial frontend tasks: say exactly which API call or hook to add, not "complete the page"

---

## DEVELOPMENT ORDER

Follow this sequence strictly. Do not jump ahead.

1. Phase 0 — Scaffolding (folder structure, Supabase client, JWT middleware, .env, error handler)
2. Phase 1 — Auth (register → verify → login → reset)
3. Phase 2 — Dashboard shell + notifications
4. Phase 3 — Tutor profile + availability + tutor mode
5. Phase 4 — Tutee request + learning needs + matching algorithm
6. Phase 5 — Session coordination (accept/decline, time slot, venue, messaging)
7. Phase 6 — Payment + session completion + rating
8. Phase 7 — Complaints + appeals + admin moderation
9. Phase 8 — Admin analytics + export

Do not start Phase N+1 until all Phase N backend routes have passing Pytest tests.

---
## External API Rules
- OneMap API: planning area centroids + venue recommendation (Req 2.4, 2.8)
- Google Maps API: internal distance computation ONLY — never return lat/lng to frontend
- All venue responses to frontend must use planning_area + distance_bucket, NOT coordinates

## PLAN.md Frontend Status Format
When listing frontend components, use these exact markers:
- ✅ Complete — UI done, backend wired, no work needed
- 🔗 Partial — UI exists, backend API not yet connected (describe exact missing API call)
- ❌ Not started

